<subSubSection id="C34F8499FFAD9366FF75FC97FAC9FC87" pageId="5" pageNumber="538" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEAD712FFAD9366FF75FC97FAC9FC87" blockId="5.[151,1437,780,2030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAD9366FF75FC97FED7FCEB" bold="true" box="[151,276,780,806]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Body (
<figureCitation id="136ECB97FFAD9366FE8BFC97FE32FCEB" box="[361,497,780,806]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–24" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[300,1336,215,1749]" captionTargetId="figure-17@11.[182,1406,178,1880]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 19–24. 19, 21, 23, (dorsal habitus): 19, Aethina (Idaethina) orientalis (Nietner, 1856); 21, Aethina (Idaethina) subrugosa (Grouvelle, 1894); 23, Aethina (Circopes) subquadrata (Motschulsky, 1858); 20, 22, 24, (ventral habitus): 20, Aethina (Idaethina) orientalis (Nietner, 1856); 22, Aethina (Idaethina) subrugosa (Grouvelle, 1894); 24, Aethina (Circopes) subquadrata (Motschulsky, 1858)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417011" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417011/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Figs. 23, 24</figureCitation>
) oval, yellowish brown to reddish brown, concolorous. Apex of pygidium truncate and basal margin undulated. Dorsum covered with dense, rather long, thick, golden, decumbent setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34F8499FFAD9366FF25FCCFFECCF893" pageId="5" pageNumber="538" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BEAD712FFAD9366FF25FCCFFD95FC33" blockId="5.[151,1437,780,2030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAD9366FF25FCCFFEC7FCA3" box="[199,260,852,878]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Head</emphasis>
transverse, about as broad as long; punctation on frons round, distinct, diameter about the size of the eye facets, separated by about 1–2 diameter of punctures; punctures on vertex coarse and round, about 2× of eye facets; setae on frons moderately long and dense, decumbent; eyes large and moderately projected, about 0.3× as long as head, outer margin rounded, finely facetted. Antenna about 1.1× as long as head; antennal club about 1.4× as long as broad, about 0.3× as long as antenna.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEAD712FFAD9366FF25FB93FA4CFBA7" blockId="5.[151,1437,780,2030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAD9366FF25FB93FEFAFBEF" box="[199,313,1032,1058]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Prothorax</emphasis>
transverse (l.0: 1.9), anterior margin deeply emarginate; sides arcuate, posterior margin bisinuate, anterior angle sharply obtuse, posterior angle somewhat pointed. Pronotum rather convex, surface punctate, punctures separated on top of pronotal disc by 0.5–1 diameter; moderately long, decumbent setae present on disc.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEAD712FFAD9366FF25FBEFFEBAFB1B" blockId="5.[151,1437,780,2030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAD9366FF25FBEFFEB9FB43" box="[199,378,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Scutellar shield</emphasis>
transverse, about 1.9× as broad as long, boat-shaped with rounded apex, corners rounded; punctures finer than those on pronotum, separated by 2–5 diameters of puncture, setae short, thick, decumbent, posteriorly directed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEAD712FFAD9366FF25FB7BFAA9FA8F" blockId="5.[151,1437,780,2030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAD9366FF25FB7BFECEFB37" box="[199,269,1248,1274]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Elytra</emphasis>
together about 1.1× as broad as long, anterior margin somewhat loosely fitting with posterior margin of prothorax, humeral angles nearly right-angled with corners somewhat rounded, sides uniformly arcuate, apices separately rounded; punctures shallow, indistinct; setae rather long, dense, semi-erect and posteriorly directed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEAD712FFAD9366FF25FAD7FE2DFA63" blockId="5.[151,1437,780,2030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Exposed portion of abdominal tergites about 3.1× as broad as long, anal sclerite in males usually not visible from underneath the pygidium; surface punctate-pubescent with setae short, closely appressed to the surface of the abdomen, posteriorly directed.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEAD712FFAD9366FF25FA23FB57F9F3" blockId="5.[151,1437,780,2030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAD9366FF25FA23FEDBFA1F" box="[199,280,1464,1490]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Ventral</emphasis>
side testaceous-brown with meso-metaventrite and abdominal ventrite I somewhat darker than the rest of the ventral surface; gular region of head with subparallel antennal grooves running posterad. A median longitudinal carina present on mesoventrite; metaventrite densely punctate, mesocoxal lines reaching almost up to the length of the metaventral-metanepisternal suture from base, thereby making a distinct axillary space.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEAD712FFAD9366FF25F9D3FD1AF967" blockId="5.[151,1437,780,2030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAD9366FF25F9D3FEF7F9AF" box="[199,308,1608,1634]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Aedeagus</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="136ECB97FFAD9366FEA7F9D3FE3FF9AF" box="[325,508,1608,1634]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–39" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1791,1815]" captionTargetBox="[252,1342,217,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-25@12.[217,1371,178,1767]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25–39. Aethina (Circopes) subquadrata (Motschulsky, 1858): 25–29: 25, abdomen with pygidium, dorsal view, photograph; 26, male genitalia with tegmen and median lobe, microphotograph; 27, ovipositor, microphotograph; 28, male genitalia: tegmen, line drawing; 29, male genitalia: median lobe, line drawing; Aethina (Aethina) vicina Grouvelle, 1894: 30–31, 34–35: 30, male genitalia: tegmen, line drawing (derived from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 31, male genitalia: median lobe, line drawing (derived from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 34, dorsal habitus; 35, ventral habitus. Aethina (Aethina) nigrocastanea Grouvelle, 1903: 32–33, 36–39; 32, male genitalia: tegmen, line drawing; 33, male genitalia: median lobe, line drawing; 36, ventral habitus, photograph; 37, dorsal habitus; 38, male genitalia: tegmen, microphotograph; 39, male genitalia: median lobe, microphotograph." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417013/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Figs. 26, 28–29</figureCitation>
): Parameres U-shaped, with sub-parallel sides and rounded apex, setae of varying length present from posterior fourth and apical margin, setae on apical margin longer. Median lobe broadly elongate with nipple-shaped apex and rounded basal margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEAD712FFAD9366FF25F92FFF2DF93F" blockId="5.[151,1437,780,2030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAD9366FF25F92FFEFCF903" box="[199,319,1716,1742]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Ovipositor</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="136ECB97FFAD9366FEB3F92FFE66F903" box="[337,421,1716,1742]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–39" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1791,1815]" captionTargetBox="[252,1342,217,1754]" captionTargetId="figure-25@12.[217,1371,178,1767]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25–39. Aethina (Circopes) subquadrata (Motschulsky, 1858): 25–29: 25, abdomen with pygidium, dorsal view, photograph; 26, male genitalia with tegmen and median lobe, microphotograph; 27, ovipositor, microphotograph; 28, male genitalia: tegmen, line drawing; 29, male genitalia: median lobe, line drawing; Aethina (Aethina) vicina Grouvelle, 1894: 30–31, 34–35: 30, male genitalia: tegmen, line drawing (derived from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 31, male genitalia: median lobe, line drawing (derived from Kirejtshuk, 1986); 34, dorsal habitus; 35, ventral habitus. Aethina (Aethina) nigrocastanea Grouvelle, 1903: 32–33, 36–39; 32, male genitalia: tegmen, line drawing; 33, male genitalia: median lobe, line drawing; 36, ventral habitus, photograph; 37, dorsal habitus; 38, male genitalia: tegmen, microphotograph; 39, male genitalia: median lobe, microphotograph." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417013/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) with distinct paraprocts, valvifers, coxites and styli. Styli arise from sides of apices of coxites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEAD712FFAD9366FF25F966FECCF893" blockId="5.[151,1437,780,2030]" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">
<emphasis id="B9210B00FFAD9366FF25F966FEAAF8DB" box="[199,361,1789,1814]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="538">Measurements</emphasis>
